note: Hunter is going to be a cheat code in IDP but it remains to be seen how much value he will provide as a WR in general. For our purposes, Hunter is a DB1 as long as he is getting more than 40 percent of the snaps on offense. They will scheme Hunter touches, so, even if he is playing part time he will be able to produce enough fantasy points to be a weekly top-12 option.
Roquan is one of the safest options week to week and is a top three option for Sunday Night Football against the Buffalo Bills.
Spillane is changing teams but we still have him penciled in as a top-10 option for the season. Treat him as such for a Week 1 revenge game.

Henley is on the cusp of being in the weekly top-15 conversation, but will need to start hot to cement himself as belonging in it. Tap him as an LB2 with LB1 upside for Week 1 against the Kansas City Chiefs.

Azeez remains the Texans' linebacker to target, at least as far as the LB1 conversation is concerned. Hentry To'oTo'o is slated to start beside him, but faces fierce competition from others in the LB room, Azeez's snaps should be relatively safe. Tap Azeez as an LB1 option for a plus Week 1 matchup against the Los Angeles Rams.
Lavonte continues to get it done as an LB1 option and should be treated as such for a tasty Week 1 matchup against Bijan Robinson and the Atlanta Falcons.
Campbell should see plenty of work in Week 1, making him an LB3 with LB2 upside against the Packers.
Carson is an easy LB2 option for Week 1. He has been thrust into an immediate starting role due to multiple injuries and should be a difference maker for fantasy.

Quay has flashed LB1 upside but needs to show more consistency before he can be trusted as a top-15 option. Tap him as an elite LB2 option for Week 1, thanks to a plus matchup against the Detroit Lions.

Bolton did not take the leap many hoped for in 2024 but remains a strong top-15 option for the season. Treat him as an LB1 option for Week 1, thanks to a plus matchup against the Los Angeles Chargers.

Landman is expected to pace the Rams' linebacker room in tackles this season and should push for top-25 numbers on a weekly basis en route to a top-20 level finish. Start him with confidence as an LB2 for Week 1 against the Texans.
Mr. Timeless continues to produce for the Saints and fantasy owners alike and should be counted as a top-25 option for Week 1, thanks to a plus matchup  against the Arizona Cardinals.

Dodson is listed as a backup behind Willie Gay Jr. and Jordyn Brooks, and while he is expected to see snaps, he is unlikely to receive enough to be fantasy-relevant
.
Barton will boast LB2 upside most weeks, but is more of an LB3 option for Week 1 against Denver.

Pratt is the Raiders linebacker to target in IDP as Elandon Roberts may end up rotating snaps and hovering closer to the 60 percent mark than one would like. Treat Pratt as a LB2 with obvious LB1 upside.

Murray is expected to lead the Cowboys' linebacker group in value and looks like a strong LB2 for the season. He boasts top-15 upside for Week 1, thanks to a plus matchup against the Philadelphia Eagles.
Jihaad is slated to start in the middle alongside Zack Baun and should provide immediate LB2-level value. Start him with confidence as a high-end LB3 for Week 1.

Sanborn is listed as a backup behind Marist Liufau, a sign that he may remain in this role for the foreseeable future, given his prior experience in this scheme. Feel free to move on when/if better options arise.
Treat Milano as a top-25 option for a tasty Week 1 matchup against the Baltimore Ravens on Sunday Night Football.
Tyrice offers solid LB3 value to open the season against the 49ers. He should get a steady dose of volume in the run game and should flash his LB2 upside.
Greenlaw is oozing with LB2 upside for the Broncos, but may be more of an LB3 for Week 1 due to a neutral-at-best matchup against the Tennessee Titans.

To'oTo'o is listed as the starter beside Azeez Al-Shaair and should be trusted as an LB3 option for Week 1. There is still some risk due to the talent of the names behind him, but his pass coverage ability should keep him on the field.

White's hopes of starting took a hit when Germaine Pratt was cut by the Bengals and subsequently signed by the Las Vegas Raiders. Pratt is locked in, but it is possible he passes Elandon Roberts at some point this season. For now, he is off fantasy radars.
Tranquill is a solid option for Week 1, thanks to a plus matchup against the Los Angeles Chargers. Treat him as an upside LB3 against Omarion Hampton, Najee Harris, and co.
Trevin offers LB3 value for Week 1 but should work his way into the weekly LB2 conversation before long.

Liufau will start alongside Kenneth Murray and makes for a solid LB3/4 depth piece for 12-team leagues while offering steady LB3 value for those in 14+ team formats. He has LB2 upside for Week 1, thanks to a date with Saquon Barkley and the Philadelphia Eagles.
Dennis is slated to start for the Bucs and offers solid LB4 value for those in deeper leagues. Treat him as an LB3 for Week 1, thanks to a tasty matchup against the Atlanta Falcons.
Roberts is set to start for the Raiders against New England and projects as a solid LB3/4 for Week 1. Start him where needed in deeper leagues.

Cashman will pace the Vikings' linebacker room in tackles, but Pace should show up enough to be a serviceable LB3 option who can double as an LB2 play during the byes. Start him with confidence as an LB3 with LB2 upside for a plus Week 1 matchup against the Chicago Bears.

ADG is set to start for the Cardinals and has flashed some tantalizing upside in the past. With that said, he is still more LB4 than LB3 until he proves he can hold up with a near every down role over a full season.
Chinn is listed as a nickel on the Raiders stymieing his weekly upside a bit. Move him down to DB3 status, at least for Week 1.
Chamarri emerged as an IDP option last season but is listed as a backup on the Chiefs' Week 1 depth chart. Look elsewhere for your Week 1 LB3.
Brown is listed as a backup on the unofficial depth chart. Redraft managers can move on now, while dynasty managers who can afford to, should wait a few weeks to see how this shakes out.
Kinchens is oozing with DB1 upside but should be viewed as a DB2 until he fprces his way into the top-10 conversation.

Pinnock is listed as a starter at safety for the 49ers, giving him easy DB3 value for Week 1. We will need to see if there is a rotation once the safety room is healthy, but for now, Pinnock is a DB3 option going forward.
Bullard is listed as the starting nickel which could still prove to be a valuable spot but will likely offer more weekly variance, making him more DB3 than DB2 despite the tasty Week 1 matchup.
Jalen Pitre is slated to play nickel full time, which opens up some IDP upside for Bullock. He should be viewed as a DB3 with DB2 upside for a plus Week 1 matchup against the Los Angeles Rams.
